msgid ""
"Hotkey:   :kbd:`X`, :kbd:`Y`, :kbd:`Z` or :kbd:`MMB` after moving the "
"mouse in the desired direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:65
msgid ""
"Axis locking limits the transformation to a single axis (or forbids "
"transformations along two axes). An object, face, vertex or other "
"selectable item will only be able to move, scale or rotate in a single "
"dimension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:73
msgid "Plane locking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst
msgid "Mode:     Object and Edit Modes (translate, scale)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst
msgid ""
"Hotkey:   :kbd:`Shift-X`, :kbd:`Shift-Y`, :kbd:`Shift-Z` or :kbd:`Shift-"
"MMB` after moving the mouse in the desired direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:86
msgid "Plane locking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:89
msgid ""
"Plane locking locks the transformation to *two* axes (or forbids "
"transformations along one axis), thus creating a plane in which the "
"element can be moved or scaled freely. Plane locking only affects "
"translation and scaling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:94
msgid ""
"Note that for rotation, both axis and plane locking have the same effect "
"because a rotation is always constrained around one axis. *Trackball* "
"type rotations :kbd:`R-R` cannot be locked at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:100
msgid "Axis locking modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:105
msgid "Axis locking modes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:107
msgid ""
"A and B show Z axis locking in *Global* and *Normal* orientations "
"respectively. C and D show the same situation with face selection, E and "
"F with edge selection and G and H with vertex selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:111
msgid ""
"A single key press constrains movement to the corresponding *Global* "
"axis. A second key press of the *same* key constrains movement to the "
"current transform orientation selection (except if it is set to *Global*,"
" in which case the *Local* orientation is used). Finally, a third key "
"press of the same key removes constraints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:117
msgid ""
"The orientation can be set in the :doc:`Transform Orientation "
"</editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/orientations>` selector"
" of the 3D View header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:123
msgid ""
"For example, if the current transform orientation is set to *Normal*, "
"pressing :kbd:`G` to start translation, followed by :kbd:`Z` will lock "
"translation in the Z direction relative to the *Global* orientation, "
"pressing :kbd:`Z` again will lock translation to the Z axis relative to "
"the *Normal* orientation. Pressing :kbd:`Z` again will remove all "
"constraints. The current mode will be displayed in the left hand side of "
"the *3D View header*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:130
msgid ""
"As can be seen in the *Axis locking modes* image, the direction of the "
"transform also takes into account the selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking.rst:133
msgid ""
"Note that using a locked axis does not prevent you from using the "
"keyboard to enter :doc:`numeric transformation "
"</editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/numeric_input>`"
" values."
msgstr ""

